tags: Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review: Had visited clinic on Saturday with heavy pain of roothe , Doctor took x ray scan but then doctor asked me to be on painkiller till next Wednesday as doctors for removal was not there , the next day I called up the clinic next day stating I‚Äôm having severe shooting pain every 2 hrs and having more than 10 painkillers. The  doctor replied over phone saying to be painkillers till Wednesday , they didn‚Äôt value the effects of patients pain nor health . Just because surgeon is not available till Wednesday should patients suffer ?
reply_text:
Hi; As practo has a policy of not putting name of Pt not addressing you by name-As you have put it- when you came on Saturday; it was with very severe pain and infection which is why mandatorily antibiotics was given for min. 24 hrs and ideally 3 days of antibiotics course so appointment was initially given for Wednesday ; after informing you Tuesday is the clinic s weekly off; assuming pain would have reduced by then and procedure would be comfortable. Not as you put it here- sry if it came out that way;as Saturday Surgeon is available actually.Wednesday‚Äôs and Saturday‚Äôs have been our regular Surgical days here at chisel since 6yrs now and the rest of the days Surgeon is definitely avbl on call and for emergencies only.We do try to wrap up surgical procedures by 4pm so we can follow up on our patients.

Secondly;I am 100% sure I have not spoken with you again as you r suggesting here - either on Saturday or Sunday over the phone.Pls be honest- Wish when pts call a clinical set up common number; they do ask for the dr attending them by name!! If I would hv spoken with you; would have referred you to a friend or to get the procedure done after Sunday aft at any set up or called you in for pain management if you couldn‚Äôt find a surgeon elsewhere.
        The foe would have replied as per question put to her on Surgeon avblity.- as for pain management all of us drs were avbl on Sunday till 6pm and we r working on Sunday for the same reason. The rest is as per your understanding- as I would like to believe no person let alone any dr would advise you to bear with pain and wait till Wednesday to get the procedure done at this clinic only!! 
       However; have asked to go through call records to find out who spoke with you on Sunday and what exactly was spoken..As the surgeon was avbl on Monday also for an old Pt as emergency..Sorry for the experience and pain you had to go through even though the clinic is kept open on Sundays to see patients for pain relief in the least.. Hope you have completed your removal and are in a better space.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,
review:
Doctor Rashmi is a very dedicated, thoughtful, approachable and compassionate doctor. 

I have a condition called bruxism where I tend to clench my jaw due to stress.I had started experiencing severe tooth sensitivity due to this. 

Doctor Rashmi not only did a full check to arrive at the cause but also explained my symtoms in understandable terms. 

During my procedure she went above and beyond,patiently taking time and even extending her work hours in order to prioiritize my comfort.She checked- in on my sensitivity level at multiple intervals and ensured I had almost minimal pain.

She also calmly explained the pre and post procedure care and set up multiple follow-ups and has always been available to clarify and doubts I might have.

I strongly recommend her.I truly admire her approach of always going above and beyond for her patients.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Wait time,Value for money,
review:
I had consulted Dr. Rashmi Shetty twice in 2019 and 2021, for tooth sensitivity, tooth decay and dental bridge. Her diagnosis and way of explaining the problem to patient, is really good. Also, she explains the course of treatment properly and clarifies the doubts. Also, she keeps proper track of the treatment on patient's successive visits. I would also like to acknowledge and thank Dr. Archana and other assistant doctors, in demonstrating same professionalism and helping the patient with the treatment.
Yes, I do feel that the cost of treatment is bit higher but the patient gets good treatment and cure for sure. 
Overall, I would surely recommend Chisel dental to anyone!
